text: Dmitriyevka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Dmitriyevsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 49 as of 2010. There are 37 streets. == Geography == It is located 22 km from Ufa. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Dmitriyevka, Ufimsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
